<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="667" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d667">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857 T53/31.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul General at
                                    Halifax</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Halifax, Nova Scotia</hi></placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Mackay-Bennett cable that boat is due Halifax Thursday with bodies
                            recovered from wreck of the <hi rend="italic">Titanic</hi>. Are there
                            any penalties necessary preparatory to shipping bodies across border to
                            New York?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ragsdale.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>